# Softr Custom Code Skill

## What this skill covers

Two types of code blocks in Softr, plus all the events, selectors, and SPA patterns needed to write reliable custom code for Softr apps.

---

## Block types: when to use which

### Custom Code Block
- Available on Basic plan and above
- Insert raw HTML, CSS, and/or JavaScript anywhere in the app
- Code is added inside the `<body>` element
- Use for: embedding third-party widgets, custom styling, event listeners, DOM manipulation, conditional logic, integrations
- For code in `<head>` or before `</body>`: use Settings > Custom Code or Page Settings, not a Custom Code block

### Vibe Coding Block
- Uses AI credits (available on all plans including Free)
- Describe what you want in plain English; Softr AI generates the interface
- Can connect to live data sources (Softr Database + 15 external sources including Airtable, Google Sheets, Notion, HubSpot, SQL)
- Supports CRUD actions (create, edit, delete records) configured in the Actions tab
- Has version history (each re-prompt saves a new version, can restore or duplicate previous versions)
- Supports direct text/image editing via Content > Settings without re-prompting
- Can also edit the generated code directly via Content > Code
- Use for: custom dashboards, booking tools, progress trackers, calculators, notification feeds, partner portals, admin views, or any UI that goes beyond standard Softr blocks

### Decision: Custom Code vs Vibe Code

| Situation | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| Styling an existing block (colours, hide elements, layout tweaks) | Custom Code |
| Adding event listeners or JS logic to existing blocks | Custom Code |
| Embedding a third-party widget (Calendly, Typeform, etc.) | Custom Code |
| Building a brand new UI component connected to data | Vibe Coding |
| Creating a custom dashboard or tool that doesn't exist as a standard block | Vibe Coding |
| Quick DOM manipulation or conditional visibility via JS | Custom Code |

